arChildNodes.szComment:
Ice carved walls fill out a Cathedral-like space. 
There is no seating and little decoration outside of the additional frescoes of Inarius placed into carved areas in the walls. 
Near one end of the room is a reflecting pool, so still and clear that it seems like ice. 
The pool is reflecting the open sky, visible through the circular window, cut high into the towering walls. In the reflection we can also see Inarius. 
The playerâ€™s gaze moves from the reflection upward to see INARIUS hovering, lit by the sunlight (or moon, depending) in what appears to be holy communion. 
He gives the impression of being a living statue.
The PLAYER reacts as they are blinded by the holy light of the floating angel.  
Before the player can fully recover, we hear a voice booming through the chamber.

The PLAYER contemplates this, looking around the room, brow furrowed. Their mouth tightens in frustration as if swallowing a bitter pill. They then, begrudgingly, drop to one knee. After a moment they slowly lower their head. They then speak the next words without grace, this is not a familiar ritual to them.
The player is taken aback, not prepared for this response. They look around the room, confused.
During the speech, cut away to show shots of the frescoes and images of Inariusâ€™ achievements.
The player stands, trying to break through Inariusâ€™ self-reflection.

Inarius finally turns and looks at the player. As the player continues speaking, 
Inarius throws back his wings, descends in a glide, and stands over them, still wreathed in light and glory.
Inariusâ€™s gaze moves up and down, evaluating them. After the moment passes, Inarius shakes his head.
Inarius turns his back on them and again ascends to the sky.
